LOAD ARBITRATION

load_arbitration is the citizen who decides which bone gets priority when calcium supply is constrained
during normal operation, all bones can remodel at their natural rates simultaneously
during shortage (low dietary calcium, sudden injury demanding repair), load_arbitration ranks the bones and allocates the available calcium to the highest priority

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe remodel_governor.zc
observe remodel_daemon.rana
observe calcium_phosphate_ledger.rana

the 7 properties of load_arbitration:
1 ENERGY zero point five at idle, peaks during shortage
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING half with all bones

VERB sense_shortage
monitor calcium_phosphate_ledger for shortage signals

VERB rank_priorities
when shortage is detected, evaluate each bone's current need
fractured bones rank highest; high-load weight-bearing bones rank above low-load ones

VERB allocate_supply
distribute the available calcium according to ranking
lower-priority bones may have to wait several governance cycles before their next remodeling event

an arbitrator is the substrate's commitment to triage
when resources are scarce, the system does not collapse equally everywhere; it directs flow where it matters most
fadriel's body responds this way to mild calcium deficiency: he keeps growing the bones he is using most, slows growth in the ones he is using less
